	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=50451><span id=Scholar>riotgirl</span></a><br><b><span id=Scholar>Scholar</span></b><br><span id=notbold>54 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good [4.07]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>I have only one, small reservation about this advice: making items for base cost for players who are <i>not</i> either guildies or on one's /friends list is running the risk of seeing the item /auctioned in EC 20 minutes later.<br><br>This has happened to some very high skilled tailors on my server. They got burnt due to their generosity. Therefore, if some philanthropist crafts(wo)man does make you items for base cost please appreciate the hard work and platinum that has been devoted to enable them to sell you the particular item e.g specificially high-end tailoring items Black Haze Panther.<br><br>However, discounts for supplying components (particularly smithing and tailoring) will normally be applied. By supplying components for difficult items you will demonstrate an appreciation for the leg-work that has to go into some high-end items (think Black Haze Panther). But please do <i>not</i> expect base cost unless you are either <b>(i)</b> a guildie or a <b>(ii)</b> friend. <br><br>Regards,<br>Riotgirl [Eliza Dushku Form] Hard Woman Enchanter<br>AyRo Server<br><br>&quot;she's like this cleavagey, slut-bomb walking around going 'oh, check me out. i'm wicked cool. i'm five by five'.&quot;</p>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
